    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nThe `feedkeys` is useful for insert-mode plugins.\r\nFor example, we can use `feedkeys` to manage `dot-repeat` register.\r\n\r\nBut the `feedkeys` is asynchronous so the plugin that uses `feedkeys`  would be callback (or something async safe design) style API\r\n\r\nThe `x` flag provides synchronous behavior, but cannot keep insert mode.\r\n\r\n### Other solutions I've considered\r\n\r\n1. dot-register related API\r\nIf nvim allows the `set_reg('.', ...)`, we can use `nvim_buf_set_text` to manage buffer lines in insert-mode with synchronous method.\r\n\r\n2. Allows `vim.wait` to wait for the type-ahead to be empty.\r\nIf nvim allows to wait for typeahead to be consumed, it can be treated as synchronous and has the same effect.",
    "closed_at": null,
