            "body": "Unfortunately, nvim-cmp cannot solve it, but I'm writing a helper to manage asynchronous key sequences.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/hrsh7th/nvim-kit/blob/main/lua/___kit___/kit/Vim/Keymap.spec.lua#L16\r\n\r\nThis helper uses `<Cmd>lua require('xxx').resolve(id)<CR>` at the end of the key to call a callback after evaluating the key.\r\n\r\nHowever, this behavior is undocumented and may break in the future.",
